21:59.840 --> 22:02.840
Inside the cottage there is chaos.

22:02.840 --> 22:03.840
The cupboards are empty.

22:03.840 --> 22:07.840
The drawers are open and things are on the floor.

22:07.840 --> 22:09.840
Our money says Dad.

22:09.840 --> 22:11.840
Oh, my jewellery!

22:11.840 --> 22:13.840
Says Mum.

22:13.840 --> 22:15.840
Uncle Steven says.

22:15.840 --> 22:16.840
What's missing?

22:16.840 --> 22:18.840
Oh, we must phone the police.

22:18.840 --> 22:22.840
They look in all the rooms, but nothing is missing.

22:22.840 --> 22:24.840
Look, our money is here.

22:24.840 --> 22:26.840
The thief doesn't want money.

22:26.840 --> 22:28.840
Says Dad, happily.

22:28.840 --> 22:32.840
And look, my jewellery is here.

22:32.840 --> 22:35.840
He doesn't want my diamond ring.

22:35.840 --> 22:36.840
Says Mum.

22:36.840 --> 22:37.840
So why?

22:37.840 --> 22:40.840
What is interesting for a thief here?

22:40.840 --> 22:42.840
Ask Max.

22:43.840 --> 22:46.840
Uncle Steven's face is very serious.

22:46.840 --> 22:49.840
I think I know the answer to that question.

22:49.840 --> 22:52.840
This is what the thief wants.

22:52.840 --> 22:53.840
He says.

22:53.840 --> 22:56.840
And takes the book of mysteries from his bag.

22:56.840 --> 22:58.840
That old book.

22:58.840 --> 22:59.840
But why?

22:59.840 --> 23:00.840
Ask Max.

23:00.840 --> 23:04.840
I am studying the mystery of Stonehenge.

23:04.840 --> 23:07.840
Some people think that it is an ancient computer.

23:07.840 --> 23:10.840
Uncle Steven explains.

23:10.840 --> 23:12.840
I don't understand.

23:12.840 --> 23:13.840
Says Laura.

23:13.840 --> 23:19.840
Ancient people understand lots of things that we don't understand now.

23:19.840 --> 23:25.840
Things about the stars, about energy, mathematics and communication.

23:25.840 --> 23:29.840
We think that Stonehenge is an enormous computer.

23:29.840 --> 23:35.840
It connects information to other ancient computers around the world.

23:35.840 --> 23:36.840
Like the Pyramids.

23:36.840 --> 23:38.840
Says Laura excitedly.

23:38.840 --> 23:39.840
Exactly.

23:39.840 --> 23:44.840
Perhaps these computers communicate with spacemen too.

23:44.840 --> 23:45.840
Wow.

23:45.840 --> 23:46.840
Says Max.

23:46.840 --> 23:49.840
Uncle Steven continues.

23:49.840 --> 23:53.840
My old book of mysteries has a secret code.

23:53.840 --> 23:56.840
But there is a symbol I don't understand.

23:56.840 --> 24:02.840
I want to understand the symbol because I want to understand Stonehenge.

24:02.840 --> 24:08.840
This computer can be very dangerous because bad people can use the information.

24:08.840 --> 24:11.840
We must protect the book, do you understand?

24:11.840 --> 24:12.840
Yes.

24:12.840 --> 24:14.840
They all reply.

24:14.840 --> 24:16.840
Now, let's tidy the house.

24:16.840 --> 24:20.840
Everyone must keep their eyes and ears open.

24:20.840 --> 24:21.840
Yes.

24:21.840 --> 24:23.840
They all reply.

24:23.840 --> 24:26.840
The twins are tidying the house.

24:26.840 --> 24:29.840
Suddenly Laura stops and says,

24:29.840 --> 24:30.840
Max, look.

24:30.840 --> 24:32.840
What do you think this is?

24:32.840 --> 24:35.840
She gives her brother a small silver object.

24:35.840 --> 24:40.840
It is round with a triangle and a strange cross in the middle.

24:40.840 --> 24:42.840
It's got a pin in the back.

24:42.840 --> 24:43.840
It's a brooch.

24:43.840 --> 24:44.840
Yes.

24:44.840 --> 24:46.840
Perhaps it belongs to the thief.

24:46.840 --> 24:48.840
Let's give it to Uncle Steven.

24:48.840 --> 24:52.840
They tell their uncle the story and he looks at the small object.

24:52.840 --> 24:56.840
He puts it in his desk and his face is serious.

24:56.840 --> 24:59.840
He doesn't say anything.

24:59.840 --> 25:02.840
Max and Laura go into the living room.

25:02.840 --> 25:05.840
There's something strange about that object, Laura.

25:05.840 --> 25:06.840
Says Max.

25:06.840 --> 25:08.840
I know that symbol.

25:08.840 --> 25:09.840
Yes.

25:09.840 --> 25:10.840
Says Laura.

25:10.840 --> 25:11.840
Me too.

25:11.840 --> 25:14.840
I recognize it, but where from?

25:21.840 --> 25:23.840
Chapter Seven.

25:23.840 --> 25:25.840
A noisy night.

25:33.840 --> 25:36.840
At seven o'clock, Mrs. Black arrives.

25:36.840 --> 25:40.840
She helps cook the dinner and listens to the story.

25:40.840 --> 25:41.840
Terrible.

25:41.840 --> 25:46.840
She says, every summer there are thieves in Stone Cross.

25:46.840 --> 25:49.840
They know there are lots of tourists, you see.

25:49.840 --> 25:51.840
But you say that tourists don't come here.

25:51.840 --> 25:53.840
Answers, Laura.

25:53.840 --> 25:55.840
Oh, yes.

25:55.840 --> 25:57.840
Well, it depends.

25:57.840 --> 26:00.840
Some summers, there are a lot.

26:00.840 --> 26:03.840
Suddenly a telephone rings.

26:03.840 --> 26:06.840
It is Mrs. Black's mobile phone.

26:06.840 --> 26:08.840
Oh, excuse me.

26:08.840 --> 26:12.840
She says and smiles at everyone.

26:12.840 --> 26:16.840
She goes to the hall and speaks in a soft voice.

26:16.840 --> 26:17.840
Yes.

26:17.840 --> 26:18.840
Yes.

26:18.840 --> 26:19.840
OK.

26:19.840 --> 26:20.840
Don't worry.

26:20.840 --> 26:22.840
Everything's all right.

26:22.840 --> 26:24.840
I don't know.

26:24.840 --> 26:25.840
Perhaps tonight.

26:25.840 --> 26:27.840
Perhaps tomorrow night.

26:27.840 --> 26:28.840
OK.

26:28.840 --> 26:29.840
Bye.

26:29.840 --> 26:30.840
My son.

26:30.840 --> 26:31.840
She explains.

26:31.840 --> 26:35.840
He's 27 and he doesn't know how to cook.

26:35.840 --> 26:37.840
Can you believe it?

26:37.840 --> 26:38.840
Mum laughs.

26:38.840 --> 26:42.840
I'm sure he prefers your wonderful cooking.

26:42.840 --> 26:46.840
Later that evening, everyone is playing cards together.

26:46.840 --> 26:48.840
Mum is winning.

26:48.840 --> 26:49.840
She always wins.

26:49.840 --> 26:51.840
Mrs. Black says.

26:51.840 --> 26:52.840
Who wins?

26:52.840 --> 26:56.840
Who wants a nice cup of hot chocolate?

26:56.840 --> 27:00.840
During the evening and at night, it is cold in the house.

27:00.840 --> 27:01.840
They say.

27:01.840 --> 27:03.840
Yes, please, Mrs. Black.

27:03.840 --> 27:05.840
But Laura says.

27:05.840 --> 27:06.840
No, thank you.

27:06.840 --> 27:08.840
The housekeeper seems offended.

27:08.840 --> 27:09.840
Why not?

27:09.840 --> 27:11.840
She asks angrily.

27:11.840 --> 27:13.840
Hot chocolate helps you sleep.

27:13.840 --> 27:16.840
I can sleep with no problems, thank you.

27:16.840 --> 27:18.840
Replies Laura.

27:18.840 --> 27:20.840
Mrs. Black is not very happy.

27:20.840 --> 27:23.840
But goes to the kitchen to make hot chocolate for the others.

27:23.840 --> 27:27.840
It is creamy, chocolatey and delicious.

27:27.840 --> 27:30.840
This is wonderful, Mrs. Black.

27:30.840 --> 27:33.840
What is the special ingredient?

27:33.840 --> 27:35.840
Do you have a secret recipe?

27:35.840 --> 27:37.840
Asks mum.

27:37.840 --> 27:41.840
It's my grandmother's secret recipe.

27:41.840 --> 27:44.840
She says and laughs.

27:44.840 --> 27:47.840
She says good night and goes home.

27:47.840 --> 27:52.840
Soon, everyone is very sleepy and goes to bed.

27:52.840 --> 27:57.840
Only Laura isn't tired.

27:57.840 --> 28:00.840
It is the middle of the night.

28:00.840 --> 28:05.840
Outside the sky is full of stars, but there is no moon.

28:05.840 --> 28:07.840
Everyone is sleeping.

28:07.840 --> 28:11.840
Mum is dreaming and Dad is snoring.

28:11.840 --> 28:15.840
Suddenly, Laura sits up in her bed.

28:15.840 --> 28:18.840
There is a noise.

28:18.840 --> 28:21.840
Someone is downstairs.

28:21.840 --> 28:23.840
She relaxes.

28:23.840 --> 28:25.840
It is probably her father.

28:25.840 --> 28:29.840
Me sometimes gets up and sleep walks.

28:29.840 --> 28:31.840
But no.

28:31.840 --> 28:34.840
She can hear her face.

28:34.840 --> 28:36.840
But no.

28:36.840 --> 28:38.840
She can hear her father.

28:38.840 --> 28:43.840
He is snoring in his bedroom.

28:43.840 --> 28:46.840
She gets up very quietly.

28:46.840 --> 28:48.840
Yes.

28:48.840 --> 28:50.840
There is someone.

28:50.840 --> 28:53.840
The noise is in the study.

28:53.840 --> 28:55.840
She goes downstairs.

28:55.840 --> 28:58.840
She is very quiet.

28:58.840 --> 29:02.840
When she is outside the study, she stops and listens.

29:02.840 --> 29:08.840
She hears the sound of paper.

29:08.840 --> 29:10.840
I must be brave.

29:10.840 --> 29:14.840
She says and pushes the door open quietly.

29:14.840 --> 29:15.840
Stop! Thief!

29:15.840 --> 29:16.840
She shouts.

29:16.840 --> 29:20.840
But to her surprise, she sees Mrs. Black.

29:20.840 --> 29:25.840
She is sitting at Uncle Steven's desk, reading his notebooks.

29:25.840 --> 29:28.840
Oh. Mrs. Black.

29:28.840 --> 29:29.840
It's you.

29:29.840 --> 29:30.840
Says Laura.

29:30.840 --> 29:32.840
Uh. Hello, Laura.

29:32.840 --> 29:35.840
I can't find my car keys.

29:35.840 --> 29:37.840
Perhaps they are here.

29:37.840 --> 29:39.840
I don't want to disturb everyone.

29:39.840 --> 29:41.840
Oh. All right.

29:41.840 --> 29:42.840
Says Laura.

29:42.840 --> 29:49.840
But then, she remembers Mrs. Black hasn't got a car.

29:49.840 --> 29:52.840
At that moment, Dad and Uncle Steven arrive.

29:52.840 --> 29:55.840
They think there is another thief.

29:55.840 --> 29:58.840
Dad smiles and laughs.

29:58.840 --> 30:01.840
Phew. He's Mrs. Black.

30:01.840 --> 30:03.840
Hello, Mrs. Black.

30:03.840 --> 30:05.840
You're working late tonight.

30:05.840 --> 30:07.840
Uncle Steven doesn't laugh.

30:07.840 --> 30:10.840
What are you doing in my study, Mrs. Black?

30:10.840 --> 30:13.840
He asks.

30:13.840 --> 30:16.840
She tells him the story of the car keys.

30:16.840 --> 30:18.840
Uncle Steven replies.

30:18.840 --> 30:22.840
Tomorrow, we can all look for the keys together.

30:22.840 --> 30:24.840
Now, it's time to sleep.

30:24.840 --> 30:26.840
Good night, Mrs. Black.

30:26.840 --> 30:30.840
He opens the door, and the housekeeper goes out.

30:30.840 --> 30:33.840
She doesn't look at Uncle Steven when she says.

30:33.840 --> 30:36.840
Good night, everyone.

30:43.840 --> 30:44.840
Chapter 8.

30:44.840 --> 30:47.840
Now, I remember.

30:56.840 --> 31:01.840
For two or three days, everything is normal, and everyone is happy.

31:01.840 --> 31:06.840
Mrs. Black says her son has got the car keys, and they aren't lost after all.

31:06.840 --> 31:11.840
Laura looks at Mrs. Black, but decides not to say anything.

31:11.840 --> 31:15.840
On Wednesday afternoon, mum and dad go walking.

31:15.840 --> 31:18.840
Dad wants to sleep, but mum says.

31:18.840 --> 31:22.840
No, Andrew. You can't sleep all holiday.

31:22.840 --> 31:24.840
Oh, all right.

31:24.840 --> 31:27.840
He replies, but he is not very happy.

31:27.840 --> 31:30.840
What about you, Steven? Come with us. No, thank you.

31:30.840 --> 31:32.840
I must work.

31:32.840 --> 31:34.840
Auntie Barbara laughs.

31:34.840 --> 31:36.840
And says to mum.

31:36.840 --> 31:42.840
Sarah, your husband sleeps all the time, and my husband works all the time.

31:42.840 --> 31:44.840
Don't laugh, Barbara.

31:44.840 --> 31:46.840
Replies, Uncle Steven.

31:46.840 --> 31:48.840
My work is very important.

31:48.840 --> 31:50.840
Everyone laughs.

31:51.840 --> 31:54.840
Sometimes Uncle Steven is very funny.

31:54.840 --> 31:57.840
Hm. Today, I want to work a lot.

31:57.840 --> 32:02.840
Please don't disturb me, he says, and goes to the study.

32:02.840 --> 32:04.840
Can I come with you, too?

32:04.840 --> 32:06.840
asks Auntie Barbara.

32:06.840 --> 32:08.840
Of course, they reply.

32:08.840 --> 32:13.840
They all put on their walking boots and say goodbye to the twins.

32:15.840 --> 32:19.840
Max and Laura decide to explore a different part of the village.

32:19.840 --> 32:22.840
In the village, there is a small hill.

32:22.840 --> 32:26.840
It is a strange shape, and on the top, there is a stone cross.

32:26.840 --> 32:31.840
The village probably has the name stone cross, because there is a stone cross on the hill.

32:31.840 --> 32:32.840
Says Laura.

32:32.840 --> 32:34.840
Very clever, Sherlock.

32:34.840 --> 32:36.840
Says her brother.

32:36.840 --> 32:39.840
They look up to the cross on the hill.

32:39.840 --> 32:42.840
Two people are talking near it.

32:42.840 --> 32:47.840
The sun is behind them, and the twins can't see very well.

32:48.840 --> 32:50.840
Who are those two people?

32:50.840 --> 32:51.840
They ask together.

32:51.840 --> 32:54.840
Mrs. Black and Martin Knight.

32:54.840 --> 32:56.840
Let's go and listen.

32:56.840 --> 32:57.840
Says Max.

32:57.840 --> 32:58.840
No, Max.

32:58.840 --> 32:59.840
Says Laura.

32:59.840 --> 33:00.840
We must listen to it.

33:00.840 --> 33:02.840
Suddenly she stops.

33:02.840 --> 33:04.840
Her face is white.

33:04.840 --> 33:07.840
Max, now I remember.

33:07.840 --> 33:09.840
Max's face is white, too.

33:09.840 --> 33:12.840
He remembers the same thing.

33:12.840 --> 33:13.840
I know.

33:13.840 --> 33:14.840
Me, too.

33:14.840 --> 33:16.840
The symbol.

33:16.840 --> 33:17.840
Yes.

33:17.840 --> 33:19.840
I know where it comes from.

33:19.840 --> 33:20.840
Yes.

33:20.840 --> 33:21.840
Mrs. Black's earrings.

33:21.840 --> 33:23.840
It's the same symbol.

33:23.840 --> 33:24.840
What?

33:24.840 --> 33:27.840
I remember it from Martin Knight's tie.

33:27.840 --> 33:28.840
What?

33:28.840 --> 33:32.840
This means Mrs. Black and Martin Knight know the thief.

33:32.840 --> 33:34.840
Perhaps one of them is the thief.

33:34.840 --> 33:38.840
Do you remember Mrs. Black reading Uncle Steven's notebook?

33:38.840 --> 33:41.840
Do you remember Martin Knight's questions?

33:41.840 --> 33:43.840
What can we do?

33:43.840 --> 33:44.840
Come on, Laura.

33:44.840 --> 33:45.840
Follow me.

33:45.840 --> 33:46.840
Mrs. Max.

33:46.840 --> 33:48.840
They start to go up the hill.

33:48.840 --> 33:51.840
But Mrs. Black and Martin Knight aren't there.

33:51.840 --> 33:53.840
We're too late.

33:53.840 --> 33:54.840
Where are they now?

33:54.840 --> 33:55.840
Says Laura.

33:55.840 --> 33:56.840
I don't know.

33:56.840 --> 33:57.840
Answers Max.

33:57.840 --> 33:58.840
Come on.

33:58.840 --> 34:01.840
Let's go home and tell Uncle Steven what we know.

34:01.840 --> 34:03.840
They start to walk home.

34:03.840 --> 34:07.840
But on the hill, two dark shadows are watching them.

34:07.840 --> 34:10.840
From behind the stone cross.

34:11.840 --> 34:13.840
Famous Detectives.

34:13.840 --> 34:16.840
The Famous Five by Enid Blighten.

34:16.840 --> 34:21.840
The Famous Five are a group of child detectives.

34:21.840 --> 34:25.840
Really four children and a dog.

34:25.840 --> 34:30.840
Three of the children, Julian, Dick and Anne,

34:30.840 --> 34:33.840
are brothers and sister.

34:33.840 --> 34:37.840
During their holidays, they usually go to stay with them.

34:37.840 --> 34:45.840
During their holidays, they usually go to stay with their aunt, uncle and cousin Georgina.

34:45.840 --> 34:52.840
Georgina prefers the name George and has a dog called Timmy.

34:52.840 --> 34:59.840
The Five always have adventures and solve mysteries.

34:59.840 --> 35:03.840
Miss Marple by Agatha Christie.

35:04.840 --> 35:08.840
Another famous detective is an old lady with white hair.

35:08.840 --> 35:12.840
Her name is Miss Marple.

35:12.840 --> 35:16.840
She is about 70 and she's not married.

35:16.840 --> 35:22.840
She lives in a very small village in England, like Stone Cross.

35:22.840 --> 35:29.840
It is a quiet village, but Miss Marple meets lots of people there.

35:29.840 --> 35:34.840
A postman, a village policeman, a hairdresser.

35:34.840 --> 35:39.840
She talks to these people and listens to their stories.

35:39.840 --> 35:46.840
She discovers lots of information about crime.

35:47.840 --> 35:53.840
Chapter 9.

35:53.840 --> 35:58.840
Uncle Stephen understands.

36:05.840 --> 36:07.840
Uncle Stephen is happy.

36:07.840 --> 36:10.840
Finally, he can work in peace.

36:10.840 --> 36:14.840
He makes a cup of tea and goes into his study.

36:15.840 --> 36:22.840
On his desk, there is the old book of mysteries and the silver broach with the strange symbol.

36:22.840 --> 36:26.840
He takes the broach in his hand and looks at it.

36:26.840 --> 36:30.840
He knows it is part of the mystery, but how?

36:30.840 --> 36:33.840
The circle is similar to Stonehenge.

36:33.840 --> 36:37.840
The triangle is similar to the hills around it.

36:37.840 --> 36:40.840
But what does the cross mean?

36:41.840 --> 36:46.840
Uncle Stephen recognizes the symbol, but where from?

36:46.840 --> 36:49.840
He drinks some more tea.

36:49.840 --> 36:51.840
He thinks.

36:51.840 --> 36:54.840
He looks out of the window.

36:54.840 --> 37:02.840
From the window he can see the strange hill in the village and the strange stone cross on the top of it.

37:02.840 --> 37:05.840
Wait a minute, he thinks.

37:05.840 --> 37:08.840
The strange stone cross.

37:08.840 --> 37:10.840
He looks at the broach.

37:10.840 --> 37:13.840
Yes, it's the same.

37:13.840 --> 37:17.840
He quickly turns to a page in his old book of mysteries.

37:17.840 --> 37:19.840
He reads something and shouts.

37:19.840 --> 37:22.840
Yes, now I understand.

37:22.840 --> 37:24.840
Now I understand.

37:24.840 --> 37:28.840
I must telephone Professor Johnson in London.

37:28.840 --> 37:31.840
He takes the phone and calls the number.

37:31.840 --> 37:33.840
Hello, Professor.

37:33.840 --> 37:36.840
It's Stephen Morrell here.

37:36.840 --> 37:39.840
Listen, we must meet.

37:39.840 --> 37:42.840
Can I bring the book to you in London?

37:42.840 --> 37:44.840
It's not safe here.

37:44.840 --> 37:46.840
There's a train at five o'clock this evening.

37:46.840 --> 37:49.840
It gets to London at seven o'clock.

37:49.840 --> 37:53.840
Yes, see you at the station.

37:53.840 --> 37:55.840
Goodbye, and thank you.

37:55.840 --> 37:59.840
He puts the phone down and picks up his cup of tea.

37:59.840 --> 38:02.840
I'm sure that tea's cold now.

38:02.840 --> 38:05.840
Says a cold voice behind him.

38:05.840 --> 38:09.840
He turns quickly and sees the shadow of Mrs. Black in the door.

38:09.840 --> 38:11.840
What are you doing here?

38:11.840 --> 38:12.840
He asks angrily.

38:12.840 --> 38:14.840
You don't work today.

38:14.840 --> 38:15.840
What do you want?

38:15.840 --> 38:18.840
Mrs. Black's earrings shine in the sun.

38:18.840 --> 38:21.840
You know what I want, Morrell.

38:21.840 --> 38:25.840
She says, give me that book.

38:26.840 --> 38:29.840
Listening activity.

38:39.840 --> 38:41.840
Hello, Professor.

38:41.840 --> 38:43.840
It's Stephen Morrell here.

38:43.840 --> 38:45.840
Morning, Morrell. How are you?

38:45.840 --> 38:47.840
Not bad. Thank you, Professor.

38:47.840 --> 38:48.840
And you?

38:48.840 --> 38:49.840
Fine, thanks.

38:49.840 --> 38:51.840
Listen, we must meet.

38:51.840 --> 38:54.840
Can I bring the book to you in London?

38:54.840 --> 38:55.840
Yes, but why?

38:55.840 --> 38:57.840
It's not safe here.

38:57.840 --> 38:58.840
I understand.

38:58.840 --> 39:00.840
What time can you arrive in London?

39:00.840 --> 39:03.840
There's a train at five o'clock this evening.

39:03.840 --> 39:05.840
It gets to London at seven o'clock.

39:05.840 --> 39:08.840
Hmm, seven o'clock this evening.

39:08.840 --> 39:10.840
All right, see you at the station.

39:10.840 --> 39:12.840
Yes, see you at the station.

39:12.840 --> 39:13.840
All right, Morrell.

39:13.840 --> 39:14.840
Goodbye.

39:14.840 --> 39:16.840
Goodbye, and thank you.

39:24.840 --> 39:26.840
Chapter ten.

39:26.840 --> 39:28.840
A doctor's visit.

39:37.840 --> 39:41.840
Max and Laura play near a river for some time,

39:41.840 --> 39:44.840
but later go back to the cottage.

39:44.840 --> 39:46.840
Everything is quiet.

39:46.840 --> 39:49.840
They don't have a key, so they knock on the door.

39:49.840 --> 39:52.840
Nobody answers.

39:52.840 --> 39:54.840
They knock again.

39:54.840 --> 39:58.840
And Mrs. Black answers the door.

39:58.840 --> 40:03.840
She is wearing an apron, and she has a rolling pin in her hand.

40:03.840 --> 40:05.840
She says,

40:05.840 --> 40:07.840
Hello, children.

40:07.840 --> 40:11.840
I'm making a delicious chocolate cake for lunch.

40:11.840 --> 40:15.840
Your uncle Steven doesn't feel very well.

40:15.840 --> 40:19.840
Your parents aren't here, and I want to help.

40:19.840 --> 40:21.840
What do you mean?

40:21.840 --> 40:23.840
Uncle Steven's fine.

40:23.840 --> 40:24.840
Says Max.

40:24.840 --> 40:26.840
He has a headache and a temperature.

40:26.840 --> 40:28.840
Mrs. Black replies.

40:28.840 --> 40:31.840
He works too hard.

40:31.840 --> 40:33.840
This is very strange.

40:33.840 --> 40:35.840
Uncle Steven is never ill.

40:35.840 --> 40:38.840
Max and Laura don't believe the housekeeper.

40:38.840 --> 40:40.840
I once talked to my uncle.

40:40.840 --> 40:41.840
Says Laura.

40:41.840 --> 40:42.840
Me too.

40:42.840 --> 40:44.840
Says Max.

40:44.840 --> 40:47.840
Mrs. Black is a big woman.

40:47.840 --> 40:50.840
She stands in the door, and the twins can't pass.

40:50.840 --> 40:52.840
It's not a good idea.

40:52.840 --> 40:54.840
She tells them.

40:54.840 --> 40:56.840
Your uncle is upstairs.

40:56.840 --> 40:58.840
He's resting.

40:58.840 --> 41:00.840
I want to see my uncle now.

41:00.840 --> 41:02.840
Repeats Laura.

41:02.840 --> 41:04.840
You can't see him.

41:04.840 --> 41:06.840
There is a doctor with him now.

41:06.840 --> 41:09.840
Mrs. Black shouts.

41:09.840 --> 41:12.840
Laura pushes the woman, and she falls to the floor.

41:12.840 --> 41:15.840
Max runs past her too.

41:15.840 --> 41:18.840
They go to the study, but their uncle is not there.

41:18.840 --> 41:20.840
They run upstairs.

41:20.840 --> 41:23.840
Uncle Steven, are you all right?

41:23.840 --> 41:26.840
Shouts Laura, but there is no answer.

41:26.840 --> 41:29.840
Max opens the bedroom door.

41:29.840 --> 41:32.840
Uncle Steven is lying on the bed.

41:32.840 --> 41:36.840
He cannot move his arms or legs because there is a rope around them.

41:36.840 --> 41:41.840
There is a big bump on his head, and his eyes are closed.

41:41.840 --> 41:42.840
Is he dead?

41:42.840 --> 41:45.840
Ask Laura in a frightened voice.

41:45.840 --> 41:47.840
No, he's sleeping.

41:47.840 --> 41:48.840
Max replies.

41:48.840 --> 41:50.840
Look, he's breathing.

41:50.840 --> 41:52.840
Yes, he's sleeping.

41:52.840 --> 41:54.840
Says a familiar voice.

41:54.840 --> 41:57.840
They look up and see a man in the room.

41:57.840 --> 41:59.840
Martin Knight.

41:59.840 --> 42:01.840
They say together.

42:01.840 --> 42:03.840
Oh yes, he laughs.

42:03.840 --> 42:05.840
Your uncle is sleeping.

42:05.840 --> 42:10.840
Now, we can take his book and discover the secret of the stones.

42:10.840 --> 42:16.840
Now, no one can stop us, especially two stupid children.

42:17.840 --> 42:21.840
At that moment, Mrs. Black arrives.

42:21.840 --> 42:23.840
I see you know my son.

42:23.840 --> 42:27.840
She says she is holding the rolling pin.

42:27.840 --> 42:32.840
Suddenly, Max understands what she wants to do.

42:32.840 --> 42:33.840
Quick, Laura!

42:33.840 --> 42:36.840
He pushes his sister to the floor.

42:36.840 --> 42:38.840
The rolling pin misses Laura's head.

42:38.840 --> 42:39.840
Max jumps up.

42:39.840 --> 42:42.840
He tries to take the rolling pin for Mrs. Black.

42:42.840 --> 42:45.840
Laura gets up and starts to run away.

42:45.840 --> 42:50.840
Martin Knight tries to stop her, but she is very fast.

42:50.840 --> 42:54.840
Suddenly, outside, they hear the sound of a siren.

42:54.840 --> 42:57.840
It is a police car.

42:57.840 --> 42:59.840
Quick, the police!

42:59.840 --> 43:00.840
Shouts, Martin.

43:00.840 --> 43:03.840
He and Mrs. Black run.

43:03.840 --> 43:07.840
When they arrive at the door, there are two policemen waiting for them.

43:07.840 --> 43:11.840
They put handcuffs on the two criminals and pushed them into the police van.

43:11.840 --> 43:15.840
Laura telephones for an ambulance for Uncle Stephen.

43:15.840 --> 43:18.840
Max speaks to the policeman.

43:18.840 --> 43:19.840
Thank you.

43:19.840 --> 43:24.840
He says, but I don't understand why...

43:24.840 --> 43:26.840
He stops.

43:26.840 --> 43:30.840
Under a tree in the garden, he sees an old man.

43:30.840 --> 43:32.840
Mr. Carter!

43:32.840 --> 43:35.840
Mr. Carter comes and talks to Max.

43:35.840 --> 43:40.840
Remember, boy, you must tell me your problems, he says.

43:40.840 --> 43:44.840
I know these people. I know this place.

43:44.840 --> 43:46.840
I know when there's a problem.

43:46.840 --> 43:47.840
Thank you.

43:47.840 --> 43:48.840
Says Max.

43:48.840 --> 43:51.840
You're welcome, the old man smiles.

43:51.840 --> 43:56.840
Now, how about a nice cup of tea?

44:03.840 --> 44:05.840
Chapter 11.

44:05.840 --> 44:08.840
The secret of the status.

44:11.840 --> 44:15.840
The next day, everyone is at the hospital.

44:15.840 --> 44:18.840
Uncle Stephen is in bed.

44:18.840 --> 44:21.840
The doctor says that there is only one problem.

44:21.840 --> 44:25.840
The big bump on Uncle Stephen's head.

44:25.840 --> 44:28.840
Uncle Stephen opens his eyes.

44:28.840 --> 44:30.840
Hello, Barbara.

44:30.840 --> 44:31.840
What day is it?

44:31.840 --> 44:33.840
It's Thursday, darling.

44:33.840 --> 44:35.840
Oh, hello, Andrew.

44:35.840 --> 44:37.840
Hello, everyone.

44:37.840 --> 44:40.840
What are you doing here?

44:40.840 --> 44:43.840
Don't you have school today, children?

44:43.840 --> 44:45.840
It's the summer holiday.

44:45.840 --> 44:47.840
Laura replies.

44:47.840 --> 44:49.840
We're in Stone Cross, remember?

44:49.840 --> 44:51.840
Says Max.

44:51.840 --> 44:53.840
Stone Cross?

44:53.840 --> 44:54.840
Holiday?

44:54.840 --> 44:57.840
No, I don't remember.

44:57.840 --> 44:59.840
We're in London.

44:59.840 --> 45:00.840
I think.

45:00.840 --> 45:02.840
Uncle Stephen doesn't remember.

45:02.840 --> 45:05.840
He doesn't remember about the holiday.

45:05.840 --> 45:07.840
He doesn't remember about the holiday.

45:07.840 --> 45:10.840
About Mrs. Black and Martin Knight.

45:10.840 --> 45:13.840
And most important of all,

45:13.840 --> 45:17.840
he doesn't remember about the secret of the stones.

45:17.840 --> 45:19.840
You remember the symbol?

45:19.840 --> 45:20.840
The brooch?

45:20.840 --> 45:22.840
The old book of mysteries?

45:22.840 --> 45:24.840
They ask him.

45:24.840 --> 45:26.840
He smiles and says,

45:26.840 --> 45:29.840
No, sorry.

45:29.840 --> 45:32.840
A policeman arrives.

45:32.840 --> 45:34.840
He tells them that the two criminals,

45:34.840 --> 45:37.840
Martin Smith and his mother, Dorothy Smith,

45:37.840 --> 45:40.840
are part of a secret organization.

45:40.840 --> 45:42.840
The name of the organization

45:42.840 --> 45:44.840
is the Black Knights, he says.

45:44.840 --> 45:47.840
They want to find the secret of Stone End

45:47.840 --> 45:51.840
and use the secret to become rich and powerful.

45:51.840 --> 45:55.840
Mr. Morrell is the only person who knows the secret.

45:55.840 --> 45:59.840
But I don't know the secret, says Uncle Stephen.

45:59.840 --> 46:01.840
I'm sorry, everyone,

46:01.840 --> 46:03.840
I can't remember.

46:03.840 --> 46:07.840
Perhaps it's the best thing, says Auntie Barbara.

46:07.840 --> 46:11.840
The stones can keep their 5,000 year old secret.

46:11.840 --> 46:15.840
It's not right to take it from them now.

46:15.840 --> 46:17.840
Everyone agrees.

46:17.840 --> 46:20.840
Perhaps we can find another secret next holiday.

46:20.840 --> 46:23.840
Say Max and Laura together.

46:23.840 --> 46:26.840
Perhaps next holiday I can stay in London.

46:26.840 --> 46:28.840
Says Uncle Stephen.

46:28.840 --> 46:31.840
He rubs the bump on his head.

46:31.840 --> 46:34.840
Poor Uncle Stephen.

46:34.840 --> 46:36.840
Everybody laughs.

46:36.840 --> 46:40.840
No more adventures this summer.

46:40.840 --> 46:42.840
Says Max.

46:42.840 --> 46:44.840
But perhaps at Christmas.

46:44.840 --> 46:46.840
Says Laura.

46:46.840 --> 46:48.840
Who knows?

46:52.840 --> 46:55.840
Listening activity.

46:55.840 --> 46:58.840
Hello, I'm Detective Wood.

46:58.840 --> 47:01.840
Can I ask you some questions, please?

47:01.840 --> 47:02.840
Yes, of course.

47:02.840 --> 47:04.840
Right.

47:04.840 --> 47:06.840
Just one moment, please.

47:06.840 --> 47:08.840
Where's my pen?

47:08.840 --> 47:10.840
Look, it's on the desk.

47:10.840 --> 47:11.840
Thank you.

47:11.840 --> 47:14.840
Now, what day is it today?

47:14.840 --> 47:16.840
It's Thursday, it's half past three.

47:16.840 --> 47:17.840
Oh, yes.

47:17.840 --> 47:19.840
And the month is August.

47:19.840 --> 47:21.840
Okay, let's start.

47:21.840 --> 47:22.840
What's your name?

47:22.840 --> 47:24.840
And where do you come from?

47:24.840 --> 47:27.840
My name's Laura Morrell, and I come from London.

47:27.840 --> 47:28.840
How old are you, Laura?

47:28.840 --> 47:30.840
I'm 13 in October.

47:30.840 --> 47:32.840
Have you got any brothers or sisters?

47:32.840 --> 47:33.840
Yes.

47:33.840 --> 47:35.840
I've got one brother, Max.

47:35.840 --> 47:36.840
He's my twin brother.

47:36.840 --> 47:38.840
And how old is he?

47:38.840 --> 47:40.840
Oh, sorry.

47:40.840 --> 47:42.840
Stewie question.

47:42.840 --> 47:44.840
Now, look at the photo.

47:44.840 --> 47:46.840
Do you know this woman?

47:46.840 --> 47:48.840
Is it Mrs. Black?

47:48.840 --> 47:49.840
No.

47:49.840 --> 47:50.840
That's my Auntie Barbara.

47:50.840 --> 47:51.840
Oh, I see.

47:51.840 --> 47:53.840
And what about this man?

47:53.840 --> 47:54.840
Not tonight.

47:54.840 --> 47:55.840
He's Mrs. Black's son.

47:55.840 --> 47:57.840
Oh, Mrs. Black's son.

47:57.840 --> 47:59.840
Very interesting.

47:59.840 --> 48:01.840
Thank you, Laura.

48:01.840 --> 48:02.840
You're welcome.

